article.headline: Austin Peay 72, Jacksonville St. 60
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Ala. -- Drake Reed scored 30 points and grabbed 14 rebounds to lead Austin Peay to a 72-60 victory over Jacksonville State on Tuesday night. Reed scored 20 second-half points for the Governors (15-11, 11-5 Ohio Valley Conference), who bounced back from an 88-80 loss to Tennessee State on Saturday night. The Gamecocks (11-15, 5-12) lost their fourth straight game and are battling to qualify for the conference tournament. Austin Peay led 28-21 at halftime, then Jacksonville State used a 17-4 run to pull ahead 38-32 with 14:38 left. The momentum shifted and the Governors had an 18-5 spurt to lead 50-43 with 9:26 remaining. The Gamecocks cut the deficit to 56-55, but could get no closer. Anthony Campbell added 11 points for Austin Peay. Jeremy Bynum and Jonathan Toles led Jacksonville State with 13 points apiece and DeAndre Bray added 10.
